  "texts": [
    "The heatmaps in Fig. 5d show the relative dropout of sgRNAs targeting mediators of different branches of the DDR under our screen conditions (Supplementary Data 4 and 5).",
    "Interestingly, sgRNAs targeting components of the Fanconi Anemia (FA), HR, and checkpoint signaling pathways were preferentially depleted in TMZ-treated cells compared with DMSO-treated control cultures (Fig. 5d), likely indicating that DSB are the ultimate lethal lesions induced by TMZ.",
    "Furthermore, FA, NHEJ, checkpoint signaling, and mitosis/spindle assembly checkpoint pathways were preferentially depleted in RAD18 -/-cells, indicating that cells rely on these pathways to process DSB repair when RAD18 is missing (Fig. 5e).",
    "This result is consistent with results of Fig. 1 showing a role for RAD18 in suppressing the formation of lethal DSB following TMZ treatment.",
    "Figure 5d, e also indicates minor backup roles for BER, NER, PARP, TS, and nucleotide metabolism in TMZ-treated RAD18 -/- cultures compared with TMZ-treated RAD18 +/+ cells."
  ],
